8 AS INTRODUCED
9 A Resolution declaring April 22, 2025, as Oklahoma
Agriculture Day; recognizing and celebrating
10 agriculture's impact on our state's heritage and
economy; and directing distribution.
11
12
13
14 WHEREAS, agriculture is one of Oklahoma's leading industries and
15 its associated production, processing, and marketing sectors
16 combined provide nearly 200,000 jobs and contribute more than $28
17 billion to our state's economy; and
18 WHEREAS, Oklahoma ranks fourth nationally with more than 77,000
19 farms and ranches, utilizing 32.9 million acres of Oklahoma's rich
20 land to provide food, fiber, and other necessities of life to
21 Oklahomans and people across the world; and
22 WHEREAS, Oklahoma is known as the nation's premier spot for
23 wheat production and research, ranking third for winter wheat
24 bushels harvested annually; and
